  "texts": [
    "For this, the vectors as shown in Fig. 4 are used for automatic clustering with the k-means algorithm.",
    "We initialise the algorithm with 1000 different random seeds and vary the number of clusters from two to ten to find the optimal clustering (i.e.",
    "highest Silhouette coefficient) and compare it with the semiautomatic approach.",
    "The MULT GRP, SCIBERT-HSLN and MULT ALL models perform similarly with the best Silhouette scores ranging from 0.51 to 0.59, respectively.",
    "To investigate the difference between the best automatic clustering and the semi-automatically assigned clusters, we compare the best automatic clusters of the MULT ALL model to the semiautomatic ones in Table 10."
